  "The slope of a tangent line": "",
  "A differential represents an infinitesimally small change in a variable. In u-substitution, converting dx to du (or vice versa) through the relationship du = g'(x) dx is a critical step in transforming the integral.": "",
  "A car's velocity at time t seconds is v(t) = t * sqrt(t^2 + 9) m/s. Using u-substitution, find the distance traveled from t = 0 to t = 4.": "",
  "(1/3)(25^(3/2) + 9^(3/2)) meters": "",
  "(1/3)(25^(3/2) - 9^(3/2)) meters": "",
  "(2/3)(25^(3/2) - 9^(3/2)) meters": "",
  "25^(3/2) - 9^(3/2) meters": "",
  "Let u = t^2 + 9, du = 2t dt. When t = 0, u = 9; when t = 4, u = 25. Distance = (1/2) integral from 9 to 25 of u^(1/2) du = (1/2)(2/3)u^(3/2) evaluated from 9 to 25 = (1/3)(25^(3/2) - 9^(3/2)).": "",
  "A population grows at a rate of P'(t) = 200e^(0.05t) organisms per year. Using u-substitution, find the total population increase from t = 0 to t = 10 years.": "",
  "200 e^(0.5) organisms": "",
  "4000 e^(0.5) organisms": "",
  "200(e^(0.5) - 1) organisms": "",
  "4000(e^(0.5) - 1) organisms": "",
  "Let u = 0.05t, du = 0.05 dt. When t = 0, u = 0; when t = 10, u = 0.5. Integral = 200/0.05 * integral from 0 to 0.5 of e^u du = 4000(e^(0.5) - e^0) = 4000(e^(0.5) - 1).": "",
  "A tank is being filled at a rate of R(t) = 6t/(t^2 + 1)^2 gallons per minute. Using u-substitution, find the total amount of water added from t = 0 to t = 3 minutes.": "",
  "6(1 - 1/10) gallons": "",
  "3(1/1 - 1/10) = 27/10 gallons": "",
  "3/10 gallons": "",
  "3(1 - 1/10) = 27/10 gallons": "",
  "Let u = t^2 + 1, du = 2t dt. When t = 0, u = 1; when t = 3, u = 10. Integral = 3 * integral from 1 to 10 of u^(-2) du = 3[-1/u] from 1 to 10 = 3(-1/10 + 1) = 3(9/10) = 27/10 gallons.": "",
  "An object's acceleration is a(t) = cos(pi*t/6) m/s^2 and its initial velocity is 0. Using u-substitution, find the velocity at t = 3 seconds.": "",
  "pi/6 m/s": "",
  "3/pi m/s": "",
  "1 m/s": "",
  "6/pi m/s": "",
  "v(t) = integral of cos(pi*t/6) dt. Let u = pi*t/6, du = (pi/6) dt. v(t) = (6/pi) sin(pi*t/6) + C. Since v(0) = 0, C = 0. At t = 3: v(3) = (6/pi) sin(pi/2) = 6/pi m/s.": "",
  "A company's marginal revenue is R'(x) = 50/(sqrt(2x + 1)) dollars per unit. Using u-substitution, find the revenue gained from selling units 4 through 12.": "",
  "50(25 - 9) = 800 dollars": "",
  "50(5 - 3) = 100 dollars": "",
  "100(5 - 3) = 200 dollars": "",
  "25(5 - 3) = 50 dollars": "",
  "Let u = 2x + 1, du = 2 dx. When x = 4, u = 9; when x = 12, u = 25. Integral = (50/2) integral from 9 to 25 of u^(-1/2) du = 25[2u^(1/2)] from 9 to 25 = 50(5 - 3) = 100 dollars.": "",
  "A heater warms a room at a rate of T'(t) = 4t * e^(-t^2) degrees per minute. Using u-substitution, find the temperature increase in the first 2 minutes.": "",
  "2(1 - e^(-4)) degrees": "",
  "(1 - e^(-4)) degrees": "",
  "4(1 - e^(-4)) degrees": "",
  "2 e^(-4) degrees": "",
  "Let u = -t^2, du = -2t dt. When t = 0, u = 0; when t = 2, u = -4. Integral = 4 * (-1/2) integral from 0 to -4 of e^u du = -2[e^u] from 0 to -4 = -2(e^(-4) - 1) = 2(1 - e^(-4)) degrees.": "",
  "Water flows through a pipe at a rate of F(t) = 10 sin^2(t) cos(t) liters per second. Using u-substitution, find the total flow from t = 0 to t = pi/2 seconds.": "",
  "10/3 liters": "",
